VVocal recital by K. Lahari, winner of many a laurel like the ragam, tanam and pallavi competition conducted by the Madras Music Academy, marked the commemoration of the 27th anniversary of Sangeetha Janakulam in Kalabharathi last Saturday.Grand daughter of Sastry and daughter-disciple of Saraswathi (noted vocalist), Lahari got off to an efficacious start renderingBalakanakamayachela(Atana).  Sustaining the same import of &#8216;Sangeetha Sahithyanubhavam&#8217; til\u000al the end, she renderedEnduboyera(Dhanyasi),Neevallagunadoshamemi(Kapi),Emaanatichithivo(Sahana),Varalandukommani(Ghoorjhari), all Thyagaraja compositions, andSrikanthimathim(Hymavathi) of Dikshithar. Her expression of &#8216;manodharma&#8217; especially negotiating &#8216;alapana&#8217; and swaram in Kapi and along with &#8216;neravu&#8217; and &#8216;swaram&#8217; in Ragamalika in Srikanthimathim w\u000aent aesthetically invigorating and discerningly elaborating the &#8216;Sahithyabhava&#8217;. M. Satyanarayana Sarma on violin and M. Sridhar on mridangam lent excellent support.Guests of honour, chairman of the world teachers trust, K. Parvathikumar andMihiraeditor, M.R.L. Rao felicitated her.A.R.SBottom Template Starts
